properties.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued February 5 at 9:23PM EST until February 7 at 3:00AM EST by NWS Tallahassee FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Coastal Flood Advisory, minor coastal flooding
expected with peak water levels of 1 to 2 feet above ground around
the time of high tide on Thursday afternoon and early Friday
morning. For the High Rip Current Risk, dangerous rip currents.

* WHERE...Coastal Franklin County.

* WHEN...For the Coastal Flood Advisory, from 10 AM Thursday to
3 AM EST Friday. For the High Rip Current Risk, through Friday
evening.

* IMPACTS...At 2 feet above ground, water will begin to overwash
onto Alligator Point Drive in Eastern Franklin County. Rip
currents can sweep even the best swimmers away from shore into
deeper water.
properties.instruction:
If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be
closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of
unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone
property.

Swim near a lifeguard. If caught in a rip current, relax and
float. Don't swim against the current. If able, swim in a
direction following the shoreline. If unable to escape, face the
shore and call or wave for help.

NWSheadline: HIGH RIP CURRENT RISK REMAINS IN EFFECT THROUGH FRIDAY EVENING... ...COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 10 AM THURSDAY TO 3 AM EST FRIDAY
